
# GildedEstate Development Rules

## Language Requirements
- All code comments and documentation must be in Lithuanian
- Technical terms and variable names can remain in English
- User-facing content should be managed through LanguageContext.tsx for future localization

## Technical Constraints
- Follow established folder hierarchy for all new components
- Maintain TypeScript for all component development
- Adhere to the luxury design system established in the codebase
- Use React Query for all server state management
- Implement proper form validation with zod and react-hook-form
- Optimize all images using lazy loading techniques

## Database Rules
- Follow the database schema defined in DB_INFO.md
- Implement Row Level Security (RLS) policies for all tables
- Document all database changes in both DB_INFO.md and CHANGELOG.md

## Coding Standards
- Use consistent naming conventions throughout
- Write comprehensive comments in Lithuanian
- Maintain responsive design for all components
- Implement proper error handling with user-friendly messages
- Follow the established component architecture

## Design Guidelines
- Maintain the luxury aesthetic with gold accents and elegant typography
- Use the Playfair Display font for headings
- Use the Inter font for body text
- Follow the color palette defined in tailwind.config.ts
- Implement subtle animations for enhanced user experience

## Accessibility Requirements
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for all text
- Provide alt text for all images
- Implement keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Test with screen readers for proper accessibility

## Documentation
- Update CHANGELOG.md for all significant changes
- Maintain ROADMAP.md for future development plans
- Document all API endpoints and database schema changes
- Add Lithuanian comments to explain complex logic

## Performance Considerations
- Optimize image loading with proper techniques
- Implement code splitting where appropriate
- Use memoization for expensive calculations
- Monitor and optimize bundle size
